Governor Seriake Dickson of Bayelsa State yesterday said he appointed former President Goodluck Jonathan as his Honorary Special Adviser on Education to tap from his experience for the educational development of the state. Speaking on a radio chat in Yenagoa yesterday, Dickson dispelled the rumours that he had a rift with Jonathan ahead of the November 19, 2019 governorship election in the state. According to the governor, Jonathan remains an elderly statesman that deserves the respect of all. Jonathan appointed education adviser Bayelsa govt appoints Jonathan as Honorary Special Adviser Plot to oust Dickson in 2016 thickens Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin